__

32:09.615 --> 32:12.050
♪ ♪

32:14.757 --> 32:16.347
__

32:16.365 --> 32:17.554
__

32:22.561 --> 32:25.196
Guys.

32:25.231 --> 32:27.599
I got something.

32:27.633 --> 32:28.733
What'd you find?

32:28.768 --> 32:30.402
I think I found him.

32:30.436 --> 32:31.936
He did work at the DMV.

32:31.971 --> 32:33.505
His name is Eric Latham.

32:33.539 --> 32:35.206
JOHN:
Can we be sure it's him?

32:35.241 --> 32:36.207
He went on disability

32:36.242 --> 32:38.076
September 9, a year ago.

32:38.110 --> 32:39.644
That's when the trials
were beginning.

32:39.678 --> 32:42.180
Do you think he still
has access to the DMV files?

32:42.214 --> 32:44.683
He could. Technically,
he's still an employee.

32:44.717 --> 32:47.652
He's had 32 surgeries
in the last seven years.

32:47.687 --> 32:50.355
MALDONADO: Why would he
volunteer for these trials?

32:50.389 --> 32:52.691
He looks perfectly normal.

32:52.725 --> 32:54.192
And there's nothing
in his medical history

32:54.226 --> 32:55.560
that shows he was
disfigured, either.

32:55.594 --> 32:58.063
<i>Could be dysmorphic disorder.</i>

32:58.097 --> 33:00.398
<i>He sees images of perfection</i>
<i>all around him,</i>

33:00.433 --> 33:02.834
<i>and the more he compares</i>
<i>himself to those images,</i>

33:02.868 --> 33:04.803
<i>the worse he feels</i>
<i>about himself,</i>

33:04.837 --> 33:06.304
<i>and he's compelled</i>
<i>to take the steps</i>

33:06.339 --> 33:07.439
to mitigate the disaster

33:07.473 --> 33:08.973
he sees in the mirror.

33:09.008 --> 33:10.542
That's not a disaster.

33:10.576 --> 33:12.177
VALERIE:
<i>To him, it is.</i>

33:12.211 --> 33:14.211
<i>He wants to be</i>
<i>his version of perfect.</i>

33:19.352 --> 33:21.052
Go get him.

33:21.087 --> 33:22.454
Good job.

33:37.169 --> 33:39.104
OFFICER:
Bedroom's clear!

33:39.138 --> 33:40.305
Bathroom's clear.

33:41.640 --> 33:42.741
Clear!

33:44.443 --> 33:46.644
He's gone.

33:46.679 --> 33:48.146
OFFICER: Code four...
area is secure.

33:50.016 --> 33:51.650
His terminal's encrypted.

33:53.416 --> 33:55.896
JOHN:
What do you got?

33:55.921 --> 33:57.401
DORIAN: He's using a
composite picture

33:57.423 --> 33:59.591
of his ideal face
as his avatar.

33:59.625 --> 34:01.993
His only correspondence
was with one woman.

34:02.028 --> 34:03.595
Online.
They chatted every day.

34:03.629 --> 34:05.130
JOHN:
Who is she?

34:05.164 --> 34:06.464
DORIAN:
Her screen name is Judy.

34:06.499 --> 34:07.866
They communicated this morning.

34:07.900 --> 34:09.801
They've been corresponding
for months.

34:09.835 --> 34:11.936
He told her he lives in Arizona.

34:11.971 --> 34:13.138
They've never met,

34:13.172 --> 34:15.507
but he's using his real name.

34:15.541 --> 34:17.175
I don't think she's a victim.

34:17.208 --> 34:19.143
He's perfecting
his face for her.

34:19.178 --> 34:20.612
JOHN: Have you got her address?

34:20.646 --> 34:23.047
All I have is a screen name.

34:23.081 --> 34:25.382
With a little time,
I think I can track her

34:25.418 --> 34:27.898
through her IP address.

34:30.422 --> 34:31.856
She a brunette?

34:31.891 --> 34:33.123
Yes.

34:33.159 --> 34:35.360
Yes, she is.

34:35.393 --> 34:37.295
I think I found her.

34:38.597 --> 34:40.532
The food cartridges
are in the third bag.

34:40.565 --> 34:42.132
Do you need any help, Judy?

34:42.168 --> 34:43.902
No, I'm fine.
Thank you, Phil.

34:43.936 --> 34:45.270
Okay.

34:45.304 --> 34:47.172
See you next time.

34:54.013 --> 34:56.081
(door closes) ERIC: Judy...

34:56.114 --> 34:57.549
Judy, it's Eric.

34:58.751 --> 35:00.285
Eric?

35:00.319 --> 35:02.654
I didn't mean to scare you.

35:02.688 --> 35:06.725
Your, uh...
your door was open.

35:08.227 --> 35:10.061
I meant it as a surprise.

35:10.096 --> 35:11.896
Coming early, I mean.

35:14.600 --> 35:17.068
You're beautiful.

35:17.937 --> 35:20.071
Oh...

35:22.808 --> 35:24.943
I'm sorry about the bandage.

35:24.977 --> 35:26.644
Truth is,

35:26.679 --> 35:30.215
I didn't want you
to see me like this.

35:30.249 --> 35:32.217
But I can assure you

35:32.251 --> 35:34.786
I won't be wearing it for long.

35:36.155 --> 35:38.623
I'm sure you're beautiful.

35:38.658 --> 35:41.459
As beautiful as the feelings

35:41.494 --> 35:44.062
and the conversations
we've shared.

35:44.096 --> 35:47.732
But I've kept
something from you.

35:49.969 --> 35:51.436
What?

36:08.788 --> 36:10.455
You're blind.

36:10.489 --> 36:12.590
(sighs)

36:14.660 --> 36:16.895
I should have told you.

36:16.929 --> 36:18.430
I-I struggled with it
every time,

36:18.464 --> 36:20.565
but I just...

36:22.268 --> 36:23.902
I-I just liked you so much,

36:23.936 --> 36:26.171
and-and you liked me,
and I didn't want it to end,

36:26.205 --> 36:28.340
and I was afraid it would.

36:30.910 --> 36:34.279
If you could love me...

36:34.313 --> 36:36.614
then you would see
that I am the same person

36:36.649 --> 36:38.950
that you began to know
and care about.

36:40.219 --> 36:41.620
I just felt

36:41.654 --> 36:43.421
that you were...

36:43.456 --> 36:45.590
as lonely as I was.

36:48.094 --> 36:49.928
Was I wrong?

36:54.600 --> 36:56.701
No.

37:05.544 --> 37:07.312
I don't care about your face,

37:07.346 --> 37:09.347
or-or what you look like.
I just...

37:10.850 --> 37:13.718
I'm so happy
that we found each other.

37:33.639 --> 37:35.507
You're crying.

37:42.281 --> 37:44.015
(door opens)

37:44.050 --> 37:46.418
Eric! Eric!
Police! Police! Freeze!

37:46.452 --> 37:48.420
Police!
Ms. Wood, stay where you are.

37:48.454 --> 37:50.422
Suspect on premises.

38:01.470 --> 38:04.338
♪ ♪

38:10.379 --> 38:12.346
It's over, Eric.

38:20.222 --> 38:21.656
Come down from there, Eric.

38:23.859 --> 38:27.128
Look, I understand
how you must be feeling.

38:27.162 --> 38:30.031
It doesn't have
to end like this.

38:32.601 --> 38:34.035
What's your name?

38:34.069 --> 38:36.471
It's John.

38:38.273 --> 38:41.075
Have you ever been loved, John?

38:43.745 --> 38:45.646
I have.

38:45.681 --> 38:47.815
Then you wouldn't understand.

38:52.788 --> 38:55.723
We're supposed to be loved.

39:25.020 --> 39:27.922
♪ ♪

39:40.169 --> 39:41.409
You okay?

39:41.436 --> 39:43.571
Yeah. Yeah, I'm good.

39:45.171 --> 39:47.651
Do you think, with all
the people in this city...

39:47.676 --> 39:49.110
in the world...

39:49.144 --> 39:51.624
that there's someone
out there for everyone?

39:52.581 --> 39:54.048
I do.

39:55.887 --> 39:56.927
That's old-fashioned.

39:56.952 --> 39:57.919
That's me.

39:57.953 --> 39:58.920
(chuckles)

39:58.954 --> 40:01.222
Old-fashioned.

40:01.256 --> 40:04.158
Even my robot's discontinued.

40:04.193 --> 40:05.827
Do you want me to come
to a bar with you

40:05.861 --> 40:07.195
and watch you drink?

40:07.229 --> 40:09.330
(chuckles) No.

40:09.364 --> 40:10.565
No, that's okay.

40:10.599 --> 40:12.400
That, uh... got a little
weird last time.

40:12.434 --> 40:13.835
(chuckles)

40:14.870 --> 40:17.004
Good night, John.

40:30.889 --> 40:32.129
Hey, John.

40:32.154 --> 40:33.387
Hey.

40:33.422 --> 40:34.489
You going home?

40:34.523 --> 40:36.290
Yeah, I was thinking about it.

40:36.325 --> 40:38.993
I might head out for a drink.
You ever heard of

40:39.027 --> 40:41.329
a place called Leo's? That's
actually where I'm going right now.

40:41.363 --> 40:42.563
I love that place.

40:42.598 --> 40:43.959
Come on.
You're kidding me. Really?

40:43.966 --> 40:46.467
- Yeah.
- Detective Stahl.

40:46.502 --> 40:47.602
VALERIE:
Hi.

40:47.636 --> 40:48.636
I'm sorry. I'm...

40:48.670 --> 40:49.670
not interrupting, am I?

40:49.705 --> 40:51.739
No. No, not at all.

40:51.773 --> 40:53.207
Jake, this is John.

40:53.242 --> 40:54.876
Hey. How are you?

40:54.910 --> 40:56.444
- You ready?
- Yeah.

40:56.478 --> 40:57.845
Will I see you there?

40:57.880 --> 40:59.747
Yeah. Yeah, I might swing along.

40:59.781 --> 41:00.982
You know, but...

41:01.016 --> 41:03.217
got a few reports
to finish, but...

41:03.252 --> 41:04.852
You guys have fun.

41:04.887 --> 41:06.954
Don't work too hard.

41:29.178 --> 41:31.279
♪ Worlds away ♪

41:31.313 --> 41:34.615
♪ With memories ♪

41:34.650 --> 41:38.085
♪ Of killing time and dreams ♪

41:39.354 --> 41:41.322
♪ Think of me ♪

41:41.356 --> 41:44.125
♪ It was so cold ♪

41:44.159 --> 41:46.394
♪ We burned ♪

41:49.164 --> 41:51.799
♪ And as they leave ♪

41:51.834 --> 41:54.202
♪ They cross my mind ♪

41:54.236 --> 41:55.937
♪ No time ♪

41:55.971 --> 41:58.773
♪ I think it's over ♪

41:58.807 --> 42:03.077
♪ This life inside
I seem to mind ♪

42:03.111 --> 42:08.568
♪ Look in your eyes,
you're worlds away... ♪

